Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.84,0:48:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,does. Thank you. Quick question. You and I think it was Eye of the Eye or Eye were speaking
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.38,0:48:56.11,Default,,0,0,0,,about how Freud is at 499. Yes. The level of the intellect is limited there. Yet Young
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.11,0:49:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,is at 540. 520. Yes. 520 or something. And surpassed the level of the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.61,0:49:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Could you just explain a little bit about what he did that got him past that?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.88,0:49:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well Carl Young was just more evolved. Don't forget he was looking at different aspects
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.38,0:49:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that were more aligned with spirituality. Freud was looking more at the animal nature
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.21,0:49:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego. So he saw the animal drives. Of course the deepest level of the unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.21,0:49:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,he called the id. Or all the socially objectionable. The desire to kill other people. And then
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.59,0:49:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the ego, etc. was because of guilt, which he called the superego, driven to the level
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.34,0:49:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of unconsciousness, which is the id. The ego then had the job of how to keep things repressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.65,0:49:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So Anna Freud described a very useful, I thought Anna Freud's work was great, the mechanisms
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.63,0:50:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego. Undoing, identification with the aggressor, projection, repression. So repression,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.21,0:50:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you just have amnesia. You don't even remember it. Projection, it isn't me that's that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.44,0:50:14.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's those selfish people out there. Splitting means you split people into the good and the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.44,0:50:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,bad, see? But these are from your own unconscious. The shadow gets projected onto the bad people
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.09,0:50:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the world. So these mechanisms are to a spiritual student. You run across them because
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.92,0:50:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you're doing spiritual work to undo the ego. And you see yourself utilizing the same mechanisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.07,0:50:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You see? And interjecting things and identifying with them. People get overly upset about
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.55,0:50:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,what goes on in society because they're interjecting that society. That society isn't you. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.23,0:50:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,got nothing to do with you, for God's sake. It's, you know. So the identification with
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.82,0:50:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,society. So all these mechanisms, I think in what I write, I do mention them because
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.88,0:51:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I think every spiritual student comes face to face with them. Come face to face with
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.98,0:51:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,them. See?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.40,0:51:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And what Freud would say is the world that you see is all projections from your own unconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.32,0:51:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The evil doers that you see out there now on the other side of the world, that's your
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.05,0:51:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,own dark shadow projected onto the world. And you see it as being out there. That's actually
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.71,0:51:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,your collector. That's really in you. So there's a lot of value in understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.90,0:51:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,evil mechanisms, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.71,0:51:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And so Jung just took it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:34.82,0:51:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jung investigated it somewhat differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.73,0:51:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,See? Jung...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.48,0:51:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.55,0:51:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He was looking at the collective, the collective consciousness, and he saw that universally
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.84,0:51:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,there were certain symbols and things recurring throughout societies, recurrently, the archetype
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.26,0:51:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of the good mother, the archetype of the bad mother, the warrior, which we mentioned here,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.34,0:51:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,the warrior, very important for the spiritual people.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.59,0:52:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw the recurrence of the symbols over and over in society, primitive society, more
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.48,0:52:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced society, the recurrence of these symbols, and so he studied the part that they
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.30,0:52:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,play in unconscious mechanisms and symbolization, you know, but he validated the spiritual as
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.78,0:52:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,a reality, and Freud really viewed it as an escape from reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.21,0:52:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual in him was more an escape, a denial, and so each one contributed, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.03,0:52:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,in a different way.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.78,0:52:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one contributed of great value.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.86,0:52:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
