Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.78,0:53:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.78,0:53:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes the difference in who has a big influence and who doesn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.78,0:53:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.78,0:54:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What makes the difference in the field of influence that a person has?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.28,0:54:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not their consciousness level because both high consciousness and low consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.48,0:54:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,people have influence the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.88,0:54:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget the power that is given to a politician is projection from the populace.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.73,0:54:17.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Hitler in the beginning…
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.73,0:54:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The same as Napoleon, calibrated around 450.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.19,0:54:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Both Napoleon and Hitler started out as integrists for socialism, the betterment of Europe, mankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.42,0:54:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They both made great contributions to society.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:31.73,0:54:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hitler helped the economy, created the Audubon system, many other things that are beneficial,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.13,0:54:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,zoos or something good.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.23,0:54:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And then at a certain point, he turned, you see, but the world doesn't know that he
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.05,0:54:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,turned.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.05,0:54:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The world sees him the same as they always saw him.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.65,0:54:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.65,0:54:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So, Napoleon crowned himself emperor, put himself above the church.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.86,0:54:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.86,0:54:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The pope always crowned the emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.86,0:55:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Napoleon crowned himself as emperor.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.67,0:55:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When he did, his calibrated level of consciousness dropped because he was usurping what was understood
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.05,0:55:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,as a right that emanated from God and he took on that godness himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.44,0:55:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Hitler made the same mistake, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.42,0:55:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So megalomania.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.42,0:55:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So, having great power, you know.
